# Relay — a ChatGPT-style chat app

FastAPI backend + a vanilla HTML/JS chat UI. Streams responses token-by-token
like ChatGPT, keeps conversation history in SQLite, and is built on Claude
via the Anthropic API (swap-able for OpenAI — see "Using a different model" below).

## Project layout

```
chatgpt-clone/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py          FastAPI app + streaming /messages endpoint
│   ├── database.py      SQLite layer (conversations + messages)
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   └── .env.example
└── frontend/
    └── index.html       Single-file chat UI (sidebar + streaming chat pane)
```

## 1. Backend setup

```bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

cp .env.example .env
# then edit .env and add your ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# (get one at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys)

uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

Your API is now live at `http://localhost:8000`. Check `http://localhost:8000/api/health`.

## 2. Frontend setup

No build step — just serve the static file:

```bash
cd frontend
python3 -m http.server 5500
```

Open `http://localhost:5500` in your browser.

(If you open `index.html` directly via `file://`, some browsers block the
fetch calls — serving it over `http://` avoids that.)

## How it works

- **POST /api/conversations** — creates a new chat, returns its id.
- **POST /api/conversations/{id}/messages** — saves your message, then opens
  a streaming connection (Server-Sent Events) to the model and forwards each
  token to the browser as it's generated, exactly like ChatGPT's typing effect.
- Each conversation's full message history is sent back to the model on every
  turn, so it has context — this is how all chat APIs maintain memory (there's
  no server-side "session" inside the model itself).
- Messages are persisted to `backend/chat.db` (SQLite), so history survives restarts.

## Using a different model

The backend only touches the model in one place — `client.messages.stream(...)`
in `main.py`. To swap in OpenAI's API instead:

```python
from openai import AsyncOpenAI
client = AsyncOpenAI()
stream = await client.chat.completions.create(
    model="gpt-4o", messages=model_messages, stream=True
)
async for chunk in stream:
    delta = chunk.choices[0].delta.content or ""
    ...
```

The rest of the app (database, SSE plumbing, frontend) doesn't need to change.

## Where to take this next

- **Auth**: add user accounts (e.g. `fastapi-users` or a simple JWT layer) so
  conversations are scoped per user instead of global.
- **Editing/regenerating messages**: add `PATCH`/`POST /regenerate` endpoints.
- **File uploads / images**: Anthropic's API accepts images and PDFs in the
  `content` array — extend `SendMessageRequest` to accept attachments.
- **Deploy**: backend to Railway/Render/Fly.io (needs a persistent disk or
  swap SQLite for Postgres); frontend to Vercel/Netlify/Cloudflare Pages, or
  fold it into the FastAPI app with `StaticFiles`.
- **Rate limiting & cost control**: add `slowapi` or a reverse-proxy rate limiter
  before exposing this publicly — model calls cost money per token.
